GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF NORTH CAROLINA
SESSION 2025
H 1
HOUSE BILL 928
Short Title: Allow PTs in School Concussion Protocol. (Public)
Sponsors: Representatives Chesser, Pyrtle, Cairns, and Cunningham (Primary Sponsors).
For a complete list of sponsors, refer to the North Carolina General Assembly web site.
Referred to: Education - K-12, if favorable, Health, if favorable, Rules, Calendar, and
Operations of the House
April 14, 2025
1 A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
2 AN ACT TO ALLOW PHYSICAL THERAPISTS TO EVALUATE STUDENT ATHLETE
3 HEAD INJURIES DURING ATHLETIC ACTIVITIES.
4 The General Assembly of North Carolina enacts:
5 SECTION 1. G.S. 115C-407.57(b)(2) reads as rewritten:
6 "(2) If a student participating in an interscholastic athletic activity exhibits signs
7 or symptoms consistent with a concussion, the student shall be removed from
8 the activity at that time and shall not be allowed to return to play or practice
9 that day. The student shall not return to play or practice on a subsequent day
10 until the student is evaluated by and receives written clearance for such
11 participation from one of the following:
12 …
13 f. A physical therapist, licensed under Article 18E of Chapter 90 of the
14 General Statutes."
15 SECTION 2. This act is effective when it becomes law.
*H928-v-1*

